      have h_right : runWithOracle f (buildMerkleTree right) = buildMerkleTree_with_hash right (fun left right => f ⟨left, right⟩) := ih_right
      -- Simplify the root construction using these equalities
      rw [h_left, h_right]
      simp [runWithOracle_bind, singleHash, buildMerkleTree_with_hash]
      <;>
      (try simp_all [FullData.getRootValue]) <;>
      (try congr 1 <;> simp_all [FullData.getRootValue]) <;>
      (try rfl)
``` 

### Final Answer

This proof uses induction on the skeleton `s` and applies the inductive hypotheses to both the left and right sub-trees. It then uses the properties of `runWithOracle` and the definitions of `buildMerkleTree` and `buildMerkleTree_with_hash` to show that the results are equal. The key step is recognizing that the oracle calls in the monadic version become direct evaluations in the non-monadic version when using the same function `f` as the hash function. The proof concludes by ensuring that all structural aspects of the trees (such as the root values) are correctly matched. 

